pipeline_steps.description: The script extract-from-csv.py extracts the columns from source file that contains the list of GTs and maps the UniProtKB accessions to current UniprotKB canonical accessions. Creating the source file - All reviewed human proteins with UniProt keyword [KW] “Glycosyltransferase” [KW-0328] were retrieved from UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot using the following query: “keyword:"Glycosyltransferase [KW-0328]" keyword:"Complete proteome [KW-0181]" AND reviewed:yes AND organism:"Homo sapiens (Human) [9606]"” (UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot 2018_02, accessed 3/21/18).  For each entry, the UniProtKB Accession (AC), recommended protein name, and recommended gene name were retrieved. Human proteins with Gene Ontology (GO) annotations for molecular function term “transferase activity, transferring glycosyl groups” [GO:0016757] and descendants with relationship “enables” were exported using QuickGO GO annotations service (accessed 3/21/18). Proteins with GO annotations were limited to those 20,303 accessions belonging to the complete reference proteome in UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot (UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot 2018_02, accessed 3/21/18). CAZY GT families were retrieved by first searching the database for families in human by entering “9606” into the search bar corresponding to “Tax_id.” For each family with human enzymes, the list of UniProt accessions was retrieved from CAZY and filtered for accessions associated with the complete human reference proteome. InterPro annotations were retrieved through UniProt for currently existing proteins in the list, then cross-referenced directly in InterPro to retrieve all protein accessions with any of the relevant terms. Terms were curated for inclusion, and filtered for those proteins with reviewed accessions. Terms were then mapped to accessions already in the GT list, and accessions not yet in the GT list were added.
pipeline_steps.name: extract-from-csv.py

pipeline_steps.description: Using UniProt advanced search infrastructure three searches were performed UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot (accessed 07/15/2018) using the query “keyword:Glycosidase [KW-0326]” AND reviewed:yes AND organism: “Homo sapiens (Human) [9606]”, “glycosyl hydrolase” AND reviewed:yes AND organism: “Homo sapiens (Human) [9606]” and “glycoside hydrolase” AND reviewed:yes AND organism: “Homo sapiens (Human) [9606]”, to obtain the list of all reviewed human glycosidase enzymes. For each entry, the UniProtKB Accession, protein name, and gene name (primary) and e.c number were retrieved. The protein entries retrieved from these three queries were reviewed in CAZy, Pfam, InterPro and Brenda. Entries that did not have any association to be glycohydrolase were filtered out. Subunits or inactive proteins were filtered out. The entries from the three lists were merged to get a comprehensive list of glycohydrolases. The UniProtKB accessions were finally mapped to UniProtKB canonicals
